message.content: The theorem states that for any commutative monoid $M$, finite set $t$, and function $f$ mapping elements of $t$ to $M$, the product of $f$ over $t$, denoted by `Finset.prod`, is equal to itself: $\forall \alpha, \forall M, \forall t, \forall f, \; t.\text{prod}(f) = t.\text{prod}(f)$.
